  "market_context": "Week of July 31–August 4, 2023; analyst used daily charts of ES and NQ futures alongside an ES/NQ ratio chart to assess relative strength/weakness, focusing on Friday’s reversal setup and Monday–Wednesday price action around a key fair value gap and order block.",
  "key_observation": "On Friday (Jul 28), NQ showed relative strength by reaching an order block while ES only reached a fair value gap and closed below range; this divergence signaled upcoming bullish bias with ES stronger than NQ for the following week.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst introduced SMT (Smart Money Technique) using historical examples (Jul 19 and Jul 10) where ES made higher highs while NQ made lower highs/lows, indicating relative weakness in NQ.",
    "Step 2: Analyst switched to ES/NQ ratio chart on TradingView to simplify relative strength assessment: bullish ratio = ES stronger/NQ weaker; bearish ratio = ES weaker/NQ stronger.",
    "Step 3: Analyst reviewed Friday (Jul 28) price action: NQ moved up into an order block and closed inside its range, while ES only reached a fair value gap and closed below range—confirming NQ’s relative strength and ES’s weakness that day.",
    "Step 4: Analyst projected bullish weekly bias after Friday’s reversal, expecting ES to be relatively stronger and NQ weaker for the week of Jul 31–Aug 4.",
    "Step 5: On Monday (Jul 31), ES opened and moved higher immediately, nearly reaching the consequent encroachment (CE) of the FVG, while NQ lagged far behind—validating the relative strength thesis.",
    "Step 6: On Tuesday (Aug 1), both assets swept a low, but ES closed back inside the order block body near its mean threshold, whereas NQ failed to reach the mean threshold and closed outside the block—further confirming NQ’s relative weakness.",
    "Step 7: On Wednesday (Aug 2), ES again closed inside the order block after sweeping the low, while NQ respected the mean threshold then closed below the low—reinforcing the ES-strong/NQ-weak dynamic."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Relative strength between correlated assets (ES/NQ) can be objectively assessed via SMT divergences and the ES/NQ ratio chart; daily price closures relative to order block mean thresholds provide high-probability confirmation of bias before entries.",
